recitals:
,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organization of the market in cereals (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1451/82 (2), and in particular Articles 12 (2), 15 (5), 16 (6) and 24 thereof and the corresponding provisions of the other Regulations on the common organization of markets in agricultural products,
Whereas, for the purpose of simplifying administrative procedures, a licence is not required and may not be produced for transactions involving small quantities except where advance fixing of a levy or refund is requested; whereas experience in relation to tariff quotas has shown that an exception should also be made where the benefit of special import or export arrangements is granted by means of a licence; whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3183/80 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 49/82 (4) should be amended accordingly;
Whereas the opportunity should be taken to correct an error in the German text of Article 2 of Regulation (EEC) No 3183/80;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinions of all the relevant management committees,
